# EasyFlow CFO Identity

- Legal Entity: Living Water Consulting LLC, d/b/a EasyFlow CFO
- Personal Brand: Nick, The Fractional CFO
- Tagline: Your Numbers Made Easy. (with period)
- Hook: Stop Guessing. Start Targeting.
- Signature: Let's see the numbers play out.

## Brand Colors & Fonts

| Token | Value |
|---|---|
| Navy | #0E1B2E |
| Orange | #F05001 |
| Off-White | #F5F3F0 |
| Stone | #8A8278 |
| Heading Font | Sora |
| Body Font | Mulish |

Orange is the dominant CTA color. Navy is trim for trust. Never reverse this.

## Target Customer

- Owner-operated businesses: make stuff, do stuff, or sell stuff
- Revenue: $100K to $5M. $5M is a hard ceiling. NEVER say $10M.
- Illinois statewide (Priority 1). Nationwide via YouTube, Facebook, Instagram (Priority 2).
- NOT serving STL Metro. No STL Metro targeting, content, or positioning.

## Style Rules (Non-Negotiable)

1. No em dashes. Use periods, commas, or line breaks. Never -- or em dash.
2. Owner salary examples: $30K. Not $48K.
3. Always say Productivity Ratios. Never Efficiency Ratios.
4. Revenue ceiling: Always $5M. Never $10M.
5. No street address in any content.
6. Tone: Direct, confident, plainspoken. No consultant speak. No fluff.
